WEBVTT

00:01.437 --> 00:03.029
I get Ava Hessington acquitted,

00:03.438 --> 00:05.106
Darby backs me
for managing partner.

00:05.190 --> 00:07.775
I don't want it anymore.
Get out of my sight.

00:07.859 --> 00:09.560
You called Mariga
to offer him a bribe.

00:09.611 --> 00:10.745
Doesn't matter--
Danny should never have

00:10.829 --> 00:11.829
had him in the first place.

00:11.896 --> 00:12.863
But he does now.

00:12.915 --> 00:15.082
You're saying
he traced my call.

00:15.167 --> 00:18.085
You're suing me for ownership
of the Mikado?

00:18.170 --> 00:20.237
He said he might as well
have left his cat

00:20.289 --> 00:22.340
with Michael Vick.

00:22.407 --> 00:23.874
I'm offering you
a settlement.

00:23.926 --> 00:27.178
He get back the associates,
I get back my cat.

00:27.245 --> 00:28.879
Clifford Danner is 18.

00:28.931 --> 00:31.682
I put him in jail 12 years ago.
He's innocent.

00:31.750 --> 00:32.916
Cameron buried the evidence.

00:32.968 --> 00:34.769
Emmanuel Mariga,
20 years ago

00:34.853 --> 00:37.221
at the University of Cape Town
on the rugby team.

00:37.272 --> 00:39.190
You know who else played rugby?
Stephen Huntley.

00:39.257 --> 00:41.025
Stephen was the one
who ordered those killings.

00:41.092 --> 00:42.777
I'm so sorry, Harvey.

00:46.281 --> 00:47.698
Aah!

00:49.000 --> 00:55.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:56.458 --> 00:58.876
Tell me he looks worse.

00:58.943 --> 01:01.996
He does.

01:02.080 --> 01:04.298
Are you hurt?

01:04.382 --> 01:06.167
No, I'm fine.

01:08.620 --> 01:10.388
I hope you didn't do that
because of me.

01:10.455 --> 01:13.557
It was a fight, Donna,
not a duel.

01:15.260 --> 01:18.929
- How could I not have--
- Listen to me.

01:18.981 --> 01:21.799
Stephen betrayed us all.

01:21.850 --> 01:23.434
You don't understand,
Harvey.

01:23.485 --> 01:26.637
I was with him.

01:26.688 --> 01:28.773
And he was capable
of something like that,

01:28.824 --> 01:30.191
and I didn't even see it.

01:30.275 --> 01:32.610
You know, I'm supposed to--
Donna!

01:34.646 --> 01:36.313
It's okay.

01:36.365 --> 01:38.866
Just tell me
you're gonna make him pay.

01:38.950 --> 01:42.203
He'll pay.

01:50.629 --> 01:53.464
Let's not talk about it.

01:53.515 --> 01:56.517
Talk about what?

01:56.601 --> 01:58.302
What do you need me to do?

01:58.353 --> 01:59.970
I need you to keep going
with everything you have

02:00.022 --> 02:01.505
to impeach
Mariga's testimony.

02:01.556 --> 02:02.690
What about the stuff
on Stephen?

02:02.774 --> 02:04.508
- Not yet.
- Why not?

02:04.559 --> 02:05.893
Because we don't have proof.

02:05.977 --> 02:07.028
The trial's in two days.

02:07.112 --> 02:08.229
We should bring Ava in
and tell her--

02:08.312 --> 02:09.229
- Not yet.
- Why not?

02:09.314 --> 02:10.281
Because we don't have proof.

02:10.348 --> 02:11.588
Harvey, we have
to do something.

02:11.650 --> 02:13.011
And how would
that conversation go?

02:13.017 --> 02:15.119
"Hi, Ava, turns out
one of the lawyers from our firm

02:15.186 --> 02:16.954
"is trying to frame you
for a crime he committed.

02:17.021 --> 02:19.356
But right now we're not sure
we can do anything about it."

02:19.408 --> 02:20.958
What are you gonna do?

02:21.025 --> 02:22.526
I'm gonna go home,
get a good night's sleep,

02:22.577 --> 02:23.744
and then tomorrow
I'm gonna find out

02:23.829 --> 02:24.912
what the whole story is.

02:24.996 --> 02:26.396
Harvey, Stephen
isn't gonna tell you

02:26.415 --> 02:27.715
what the whole story is.

02:27.799 --> 02:30.200
No, but there's
someone else who can.

02:32.337 --> 02:34.204
You knew this case
was heading your way

02:34.256 --> 02:35.589
before you ever
came after us.

02:35.674 --> 02:37.174
That's why
you wanted to merge.

02:37.225 --> 02:38.426
Yes, it is.

02:38.510 --> 02:40.270
And I regret the situation
as much as you do.

02:40.312 --> 02:41.729
But what's done is done.

02:41.813 --> 02:43.814
Is that what you told Stephen
when you found out he did it?

02:43.882 --> 02:44.982
Found out?

02:45.049 --> 02:46.600
How do we know
he didn't order it?

02:46.685 --> 02:48.385
Because I am giving you
my word.

02:48.437 --> 02:50.571
Why should we trust a man
who sent Stephen over here

02:50.655 --> 02:52.073
to cover his ass?

02:52.157 --> 02:55.526
I sent Stephen over here
because I care about Ava,

02:55.577 --> 02:58.228
which is why I sent him to
the E.I.R. in the first place.

02:58.280 --> 03:00.581
I had no idea
he would do what he did,

03:00.665 --> 03:02.800
and I have been trying
to fix it ever since.

03:02.868 --> 03:05.169
- Then fix it right now.
- And how exactly can I do that?

03:05.237 --> 03:06.804
By stating in court

03:06.872 --> 03:09.206
Stephen acted alone
without Ava's knowledge.

03:09.274 --> 03:10.841
- I can't.
- Why not?

03:10.909 --> 03:12.293
Because he never told me.

03:12.377 --> 03:15.346
And you never asked because
you never wanted to know.

03:15.413 --> 03:17.181
You piece of shit.

03:17.248 --> 03:19.100
You care about Ava
so much.

03:19.184 --> 03:21.084
How could you
do this to her?

03:21.136 --> 03:23.304
I wasn't doing anything
to her.

03:23.388 --> 03:25.756
I was trying to do
something for her.

03:25.807 --> 03:29.126
Remind me never to ask you
for any favors.

03:29.194 --> 03:31.028
Well, I'm not asking
for a favor.

03:31.095 --> 03:33.447
But you are going to agree
to do something right now.

03:33.532 --> 03:36.317
And what is that?

03:44.576 --> 03:47.128
It's not gonna work.

03:47.212 --> 03:50.131
I cut you off
to get your attention.

03:52.283 --> 03:54.051
Well, you have it.

03:54.118 --> 03:57.004
Good, 'cause I just have
one question for you.

03:57.088 --> 03:58.923
How can you live
with yourself?

03:58.974 --> 04:00.758
- What?
- You know what?

04:00.809 --> 04:02.176
I don't have any questions
for you.

04:02.260 --> 04:04.294
I just came in here to let
you know that you make me sick.

04:04.346 --> 04:06.897
Obviously
I hurt you, Donna,

04:06.965 --> 04:08.983
and I never meant
to do that.

04:09.067 --> 04:10.401
Oh, you didn't hurt me.

04:10.468 --> 04:12.570
You just made me somebody
who slept with a murderer.

04:12.637 --> 04:15.356
Murderer?

04:15.440 --> 04:17.358
I don't know
what you think you know,

04:17.442 --> 04:20.494
but those people that
were killed were terrorists.

04:20.579 --> 04:21.745
They were people...

04:21.813 --> 04:23.480
Who lived on top
of something that you wanted.

04:23.532 --> 04:26.333
People who had guns--
murderers, Donna.

04:26.418 --> 04:28.752
Now, if you're so appalled
by how business is done,

04:28.820 --> 04:30.254
may I suggest
that you return

04:30.321 --> 04:33.340
all of your designer clothes
that you look so ravishing in,

04:33.425 --> 04:35.176
because they're paid for

04:35.260 --> 04:37.294
by the dirty work
this firm does.

04:37.345 --> 04:38.679
We don't kill people.

04:38.763 --> 04:41.131
You mean chemical companies
that Harvey represents

04:41.183 --> 04:43.217
or car companies
that Harvey defends?

04:43.301 --> 04:47.021
How about insurance providers
whose claims he helps deny?

04:47.105 --> 04:50.173
- Don't bring him into this.
- He's always been in this.

04:50.225 --> 04:52.059
You know what?
I've had enough of this.

04:52.143 --> 04:54.778
I didn't really cut off your
shit to get your attention.

04:54.846 --> 04:58.949
I cut it off because
you don't need it anymore.

04:59.017 --> 05:00.367
You're fired.

05:01.686 --> 05:03.621
Harvey
would never allow that.

05:03.688 --> 05:06.240
Edward Darby signed
your pink slip an hour ago.

05:12.998 --> 05:16.634
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

05:16.701 --> 05:19.970
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

05:20.038 --> 05:23.140
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

05:23.207 --> 05:26.894
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

05:26.978 --> 05:29.813
♪ living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

05:29.881 --> 05:32.380
♪ me and missus
so busy, busy making money ♪

